    "type": "Question",
    "name": "Question 13 @ 2016/2017",
    "Question": {
      "content": "Two charges Q₁=25µC and Q₂=50µC are located at positions R₁=3jm and R₂=4im. Find the force on Q₁ due to Q₂.",
      "type": "OBJ",
      "options": [
        "1.8i - 1.3j N",
        "9i - 6.8j N",
        "9i - 6.8j × 10⁻¹² N",
        "None of the above"
      ]
    },
    "Answer": {
      "type": "string",
      "content": "None of the above"
    },
    "Explanation": {
      "type": "string",
      "content": "<b>Step 1: Distance vector</b><br>• \\(\\vec{r} = R₂ - R₁ = 4\\hat{i} - 3\\hat{j}\\)<br>• Distance \\(r = \\sqrt{4^2 + 3^2} = 5\\,m\\)<br><br><b>Step 2: Calculate force</b><br>\\(\\vec{F} = k\\frac{Q_1 Q_2}{r^3}\\vec{r}\\)<br>\\(\\vec{F} = (9\\times10^9)\\frac{(25\\times10^{-6})(50\\times10^{-6})}{125}(4\\hat{i} - 3\\hat{j})\\)<br>\\(\\vec{F} = 0.36\\hat{i} - 0.27\\hat{j}\\,N\\)<br><br>None of the options match this result."
    },
    "topic": [
      "Physics",
      "Electromagnetism and Electrodynamics",
      "Electrostatics",
      "Coulomb's Law",
      "Mathematical Methods for Physics"
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "Question",
    "name": "Question 21 @ 2016/2017",
    "Question": {
      "content": "If 4mA current flows through a copper wire of diameter 0.5mm, calculate the current density.",
      "type": "OBJ",
      "options": [
        "1.96 × 10⁴ A/m²",
        "19.6 × 10⁶ A/m²",
        "23.89 A/m²",
        "20.37 A/m²"
      ]
    },
    "Answer": {
      "type": "string",
      "content": "20.37 × 10⁶ A/m² (Note: Correct answer not listed; closest is (b) 19.6 × 10⁷ A/m²)"
    },
    "Explanation": {
      "type": "string",
      "content": "<b>Step 1: Convert units</b><br>• Current \\(I = 4\\,mA = 4 \\times 10^{-3}\\,A\\)<br>• Diameter \\(d = 0.5\\,mm = 0.5 \\times 10^{-3}\\,m\\)<br><br><b>Step 2: Calculate cross-sectional area</b><br>\\(A = \\pi \\left(\\frac{d}{2}\\right)^2 = \\pi \\left(0.25 \\times 10^{-3}\\right)^2 = 1.96 \\times 10^{-7}\\,m^2\\)<br><br><b>Step 3: Current density</b><br>\\(J = \\frac{I}{A} = \\frac{4 \\times 10^{-3}}{1.96 \\times 10^{-7}} \\approx 20.37 \\times 10^6\\,A/m^2\\)<br><br>None of the options match exactly. The closest is (b), but it’s off by a factor of 10."
    },
    "topic": [
